WEBVTT

00:08.433 --> 00:13.433
Subtitles by explosiveskull
www.OpenSubtitles.org

00:15.937 --> 00:18.908
(LIGHT OMINOUS MUSIC)

01:33.167 --> 01:38.005
NARRATOR: Long long ago,
when the nights were still dark,

01:38.038 --> 01:41.876
the world was ruled by the
creatures of the night.

01:41.910 --> 01:47.015
Vampires, werewolves, evil
fairies, witches, trolls

01:48.482 --> 01:52.587
and many other monsters spread
fear and terror among people.

01:53.755 --> 01:56.057
But the centuries passed
and the evil creatures

01:56.091 --> 01:58.060
changed over time.

01:59.494 --> 02:04.032
The once terrifying monsters
became peace loving creatures

02:04.065 --> 02:07.036
who no longer wanted
to frighten people.

02:08.769 --> 02:11.773
Some of these magical
beings have lived among us

02:11.806 --> 02:14.842
and undetected since then.

02:14.876 --> 02:18.813
Others have withdrawn to secret
places all over the world

02:18.847 --> 02:22.518
that only can be reached
through magical forests.

02:26.120 --> 02:28.856
The story of the young
vampire, Vlad Tepes,

02:28.889 --> 02:33.095
starts right here when he
leaves our world with his father

02:33.127 --> 02:34.964
and sets off for Crailsfelden.

02:41.936 --> 02:44.505
Invited by the mayor personally,

02:44.538 --> 02:48.143
Vlad is supposed to attend
an elite school famous

02:48.175 --> 02:50.812
among mythical creatures.

02:50.846 --> 02:53.749
But neither Vlad nor
his father suspect

02:53.781 --> 02:57.752
that they have long since
become part of a diabolical plan

02:57.786 --> 03:00.688
to plunge the world
into darkness again.

03:04.158 --> 03:06.027
And where is Crailsfelden now?

03:07.628 --> 03:09.597
We've been driving through
this forest for hours.

03:09.631 --> 03:12.100
In the ass end of
the world I fear.

03:12.132 --> 03:14.735
AUTOMATED VOICE: All
right, search the ass end

03:14.769 --> 03:16.071
of the world.

03:16.103 --> 03:18.005
(BOTH LAUGH)

03:18.038 --> 03:19.541
(WATER SPLASHES)

03:19.573 --> 03:21.943
Crailsfelden is
not so easy to find,

03:21.977 --> 03:23.846
otherwise everyone
could come here.

03:23.878 --> 03:25.981
AUTOMATED VOICE: No
entry for Crailsfelden.

03:27.581 --> 03:29.251
Crailsfelden has been
the home for over 700 years

03:29.283 --> 03:31.953
to one of the most famous
magical schools in the world,

03:31.987 --> 03:35.156
The Riffraff Academy, you
nagging navigation loser!

03:39.960 --> 03:43.130
AUTOMATED VOICE: Route
does not exist on any map.

03:43.163 --> 03:44.532
Please turn around.

03:44.566 --> 03:46.101
Please turn around.

03:46.133 --> 03:48.936
Return to a marked road.

03:48.970 --> 03:51.139
Why are we stopping?

03:51.172 --> 03:52.073
What is it?

03:53.041 --> 03:54.043
We have to register first.

03:56.176 --> 03:57.078
VLAD: With who?

03:59.080 --> 04:01.015
There's no one here.

04:01.049 --> 04:03.051
(GASPS)

04:06.054 --> 04:08.524
Good afternoon,
we're new here.

04:08.556 --> 04:10.893
- Vlad and Barnabas Tepes.
- Exactly.

04:10.926 --> 04:12.193
Dark humans.

04:13.929 --> 04:14.964
Certainly,

04:16.930 --> 04:17.765
You are that.

04:19.200 --> 04:21.970
(COUGHS)

04:22.003 --> 04:24.173
(MUTTERS)

04:25.773 --> 04:28.075
Ah, yes it is.

04:28.109 --> 04:31.847
When time turns backwards,
disaster is high in the sky.

04:31.879 --> 04:34.916
One will come, three must unite.

04:34.950 --> 04:39.955
It says here, from
fools to silent heroes

04:41.088 --> 04:44.959
who tear the devil's
faith from Crailsfelden.

04:50.198 --> 04:51.866
I've got it, here you are.

04:53.200 --> 04:55.237
Welcome to Crailsfelden.

04:56.871 --> 04:57.705
Thank you.

04:58.607 --> 05:00.174
Thanks.

05:00.208 --> 05:02.878
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

05:12.220 --> 05:15.023
Somehow I thought
he'd be a lot bigger.

05:18.159 --> 05:20.162
(BURPS)

05:23.364 --> 05:25.167
Who was that?

05:25.200 --> 05:26.801
No idea.

05:26.835 --> 05:29.237
Maybe you get a little strange
if you have to guard a bridge

05:29.270 --> 05:31.673
all by yourself for 1,000 years,

05:31.705 --> 05:33.208
and that without a toothbrush.

05:34.842 --> 05:37.246
(LIVELY MUSIC)

05:49.157 --> 05:50.758
AUTOMATED VOICE:
You have arrived

05:50.792 --> 05:52.227
at the ass end of the world.

05:57.398 --> 05:59.266
BARNABAS: Well,
what do you think?

05:59.299 --> 06:01.669
VLAD: Whoa, they
all look alike?

06:01.703 --> 06:04.239
They come out of
another time, it's crazy.

06:06.874 --> 06:09.944
That's Crailsfelden Town Hall,
pretty impressive, isn't it?

06:09.977 --> 06:11.112
There's even an ode about it

06:11.145 --> 06:14.148
by the famous local
poet, Arawin Von Gotze.

06:15.282 --> 06:17.218
When Crailsfelden
Town Hall strikes 13,

06:17.251 --> 06:19.922
the world as we
know it will end.

06:23.224 --> 06:25.293
(CYCLIST WHISTLING)

06:25.325 --> 06:26.128
Dad!

06:26.160 --> 06:29.063
(TIRES SCREECH)

06:29.097 --> 06:30.164
Oh, for goodness sakes.

06:33.268 --> 06:36.205
(CYCLIST GROANING)

06:37.772 --> 06:39.174
Are you injured?

06:39.207 --> 06:40.208
No, no...

06:40.241 --> 06:41.176
What's going on here?

06:42.342 --> 06:45.780
I don't know, suddenly there's
this old-fashioned bike...

06:50.117 --> 06:51.686
Ow, what the heck.

06:55.256 --> 06:57.359
Do you think that's funny, boy?

06:57.391 --> 06:58.359
It wasn't me.

06:59.927 --> 07:01.095
Just arrived in town

07:01.128 --> 07:03.030
and you're already
playing magic tricks.

07:03.063 --> 07:05.200
Are you even in school yet?

07:05.232 --> 07:08.302
Excuse me, Constable,
but we couldn't help it.

07:08.335 --> 07:09.970
He suddenly just rode
out in front of us.

07:10.003 --> 07:12.006
But neither did I,
my bike suddenly turned

07:12.039 --> 07:13.374
into this old Penny-farthing.

07:13.407 --> 07:15.076
Make sure you
remove this scrap

07:15.109 --> 07:17.712
- from the street immediately.
- Okay, okay, right away.

07:17.746 --> 07:19.481
And you, on your way.

07:19.513 --> 07:22.350
Yes, of course
Constable, and thank you.

07:22.383 --> 07:24.720
I'll be keeping an
eye on you, young man.

07:24.753 --> 07:26.354
BARNABAS: Come on,
Vlad, it's all good.

07:28.922 --> 07:30.758
(CAR STARTS)

07:30.792 --> 07:33.729
Move it along, there's
nothing for you to gawk at here.

07:35.530 --> 07:38.133
(EPIC MUSIC)

07:46.006 --> 07:48.209
Vladdy, Vladdy, that's it.

07:48.242 --> 07:51.245
We'll live upstairs and below
I'll set up our antique shop.

07:51.278 --> 07:52.313
It'll be great.

07:54.249 --> 07:58.487
Dad, that place
is barely standing.

07:58.520 --> 08:01.389
Nonsense, absolute
garbage, a pint of paint

08:01.422 --> 08:03.758
and it'll be as good as new.

08:03.792 --> 08:06.128
And there's even
a parking space.

08:07.962 --> 08:09.531
No way, dad, we'll
never fit in here.

08:09.563 --> 08:11.333
Of course, we will.

08:11.366 --> 08:12.200
Have you forgotten already?

08:12.234 --> 08:14.335
- I'll use my Nosferatu sensor.
- Oh, no.

08:18.172 --> 08:21.176
(MIMICKING BEEPING)

08:30.218 --> 08:32.554
Sorry about that, dry throat.

08:32.586 --> 08:34.087
Help me unload this stuff?

08:38.292 --> 08:43.431
(DOOR WHINING)
(BELL DINGING)

08:46.500 --> 08:47.935
This is perfect.

08:49.403 --> 08:51.572
It's simply perfect.

08:51.605 --> 08:52.508
Take a look here.

08:54.142 --> 08:56.444
This is the perfect place
for Agamemnon Sword.

08:56.476 --> 08:59.847
Then we'll set up the
Hotz Telescope over there.

08:59.880 --> 09:03.017
And over here we'll have
the Golden Fleece corner.

09:07.154 --> 09:09.323
Vlad, what's up
with you, my son?

09:09.356 --> 09:12.426
What if I totally embarrass
and make a fool of myself

09:12.460 --> 09:14.095
at this new school?

09:14.128 --> 09:16.198
But Vladdy, they never
would have invited you here

09:16.230 --> 09:17.532
if they didn't believe in you.

09:19.200 --> 09:21.369
And I'm quite certain you
will quickly find friends

09:21.402 --> 09:22.871
who are just like you.

09:24.538 --> 09:27.341
- It'll be?
- Super.

09:29.978 --> 09:30.813
Hopefully.

09:33.147 --> 09:34.116
Get over here.

09:44.959 --> 09:47.329
You can let me go now, dad.

09:47.361 --> 09:48.396
Mm-mm.

09:49.430 --> 09:51.099
I can't breathe!

09:51.132 --> 09:53.535
(GENTLE MUSIC)

10:35.310 --> 10:37.512
Tomorrow is Vlad's
big day, Julia.

10:40.480 --> 10:42.316
I wish you could
have been here too.

11:19.454 --> 11:22.324
(PLAYFUL MUSIC)

11:28.028 --> 11:29.998
(GASPS)

11:34.034 --> 11:38.406
Good evening, Rubezal,
Treasury and Tax Office.

11:44.611 --> 11:47.314
You owe registration
fees, acquisition tax,

11:47.348 --> 11:49.617
property tax, income tax.

11:49.649 --> 11:50.617
Income tax?

11:50.651 --> 11:52.354
I haven't even
opened my business.

11:52.387 --> 11:53.555
Sales tax, school fees,

11:53.588 --> 11:56.024
garbage eater fees,
child support...

11:56.056 --> 11:58.258
I should receive child support.

11:58.292 --> 11:59.127
Not from us.

12:00.494 --> 12:01.296
You have seven days to pay,

12:01.329 --> 12:03.665
otherwise we will
attach the property

12:03.697 --> 12:05.632
and you have to
leave Crailsfelden.

12:05.666 --> 12:07.635
Please, I beg of
you, you can't do this.

12:07.667 --> 12:09.336
Complaints can be
made in the town hall

12:09.369 --> 12:11.572
between 8 a.m and 8:13am.

12:19.680 --> 12:21.116
I beg of you, please,
this is crazy,

12:21.148 --> 12:22.616
I just can't afford to...

12:29.190 --> 12:31.526
(BELL RINGING)

12:38.633 --> 12:40.735
(MUTTERING)

12:44.739 --> 12:46.108
Subtract 80.

12:54.415 --> 12:56.418
(KEYS CLACKING)

12:56.450 --> 12:59.720
Dad, have you
been up all night?

12:59.753 --> 13:02.056
Just sorting out
a few tax issues?

13:03.224 --> 13:04.426
How's it going, my son?

13:04.459 --> 13:05.627
You ready for your big day?

13:05.659 --> 13:07.294
Yeah, for sure.

13:07.327 --> 13:08.529
And I'll be ready too.

13:08.562 --> 13:10.698
The early bat catches the worm.

13:14.701 --> 13:17.304
Wow, here we are.

13:18.605 --> 13:20.674
I just need to sort out
a small teeny weeny thing

13:20.707 --> 13:22.076
at town hall, a slip.

13:23.110 --> 13:24.311
You're not coming with?

13:24.345 --> 13:26.181
I'll be back in
time, I promise.

13:27.181 --> 13:28.682
Vladdy, please believe me.

13:28.715 --> 13:30.652
I wouldn't miss it for
anything in the world, okay?

13:32.720 --> 13:34.154
BOY: Give that back!

13:34.187 --> 13:35.355
OLDER BOY: Come and get it.

13:35.388 --> 13:36.557
BOY: What are you doing?

13:36.590 --> 13:37.792
You're so mean.

13:39.860 --> 13:42.797
This isn't funny
anymore, you idiots.

13:42.830 --> 13:43.797
Give it back!

13:43.830 --> 13:46.100
OLDER BOY: Hey, fetch.

13:48.503 --> 13:49.671
The pig pack.

13:50.738 --> 13:52.507
It's three against two now?

13:52.540 --> 13:55.743
Wow, you guys are so brave.

13:55.776 --> 13:57.112
Hey, let's get out of here.

13:57.144 --> 13:58.612
We should get good
seats to the freak show,

13:58.646 --> 13:59.714
that'll be funny.

14:00.681 --> 14:03.484
And we'll see you
around, Redhead.

14:05.619 --> 14:08.388
(BULLIES MIMICKING PIG GRUNTING)

14:08.422 --> 14:09.423
Thanks a lot.

14:11.191 --> 14:13.695
That's 778 good deeds.

14:15.263 --> 14:16.364
GIRLS: Fairy power.

14:18.733 --> 14:20.167
Who are they?

14:20.200 --> 14:22.503
That was Pimple Face,
Meathead and Pig Cheeks.

14:23.704 --> 14:24.705
What?

14:24.739 --> 14:26.641
I thought you
meant the pig pack.

14:26.673 --> 14:28.375
No, that's Faye and her friends.

14:28.408 --> 14:29.244
Faye who?

14:30.177 --> 14:31.745
Just Faye, F-A-Y-E.

14:31.778 --> 14:32.746
Ah, okay.

14:32.779 --> 14:35.215
- I'm Wolf, by the way.
- Vlad.

14:35.249 --> 14:37.752
Hello, yeah, and
just so you know,

14:37.784 --> 14:39.386
I could have floored 'em myself,

14:39.420 --> 14:41.789
but then maybe there would
have been injuries and such.

14:41.821 --> 14:43.892
I prefer to stay out of it.

14:43.925 --> 14:45.827
You're going into
year seven, right?

14:45.859 --> 14:47.294
That's so cool, huh?

14:47.327 --> 14:49.898
My dad and I have been
preparing for months.

14:49.931 --> 14:51.699
Wolf, you're drooling.

14:51.731 --> 14:54.434
Oh yeah, yeah, yeah.

14:54.468 --> 14:57.739
Sorry, I'm just so
excited, are you?

14:57.772 --> 14:59.806
It's okay if you're nervous.

14:59.840 --> 15:00.673
Yeah, well...

15:03.744 --> 15:05.312
This is so great
we're on the front row,

15:05.345 --> 15:06.246
you can sit next to me.

15:06.281 --> 15:09.651
I'll take good care of
you, a big strong guy.

15:09.683 --> 15:10.884
- Wolfie!
- Mom!

15:10.917 --> 15:13.821
Don't call the boy
Wolfie, he's grown up now.

15:13.854 --> 15:16.291
Isn't that right, my
strong pot cleaner?

15:17.325 --> 15:19.927
This is Vlad, my new friend.

15:19.960 --> 15:22.397
(SNIFFING)

15:25.865 --> 15:28.302
It's starting, it's
starting, come on!

15:28.335 --> 15:30.739
(BELL RINGING)

15:42.350 --> 15:45.553
So, let's just take
a look, Witchbay.

15:53.893 --> 15:56.364
(KNOCKING)

15:57.598 --> 15:58.733
Can I help you?

16:01.301 --> 16:02.670
Good morning, please
excuse my interrupting you.

16:02.702 --> 16:03.904
Tepes, is the name.

16:05.406 --> 16:07.575
I'm here to file
a tax complaint.

16:07.608 --> 16:09.911
So specifically, it's
about these fees,

16:09.944 --> 16:11.746
you know, these taxes.

16:11.778 --> 16:13.513
There's no way I can pay this.

16:13.547 --> 16:14.749
Well, not right away.

16:14.782 --> 16:16.783
I could definitely
pay in installments.

16:16.816 --> 16:21.822
My dear Mr. Tepes, every
new citizen in Crailsfelden

16:23.490 --> 16:26.727
must of course contribute to
our small community, right?

16:26.760 --> 16:27.995
Naturally.

16:28.028 --> 16:30.931
Of course, if you can't,
you may find your luck

16:30.965 --> 16:32.633
in another magical town.

16:34.435 --> 16:35.803
In Yetipolis, perhaps.

16:35.835 --> 16:38.806
Or Mamania.

16:40.574 --> 16:45.513
But the Riffraff Academy,
there's only one of those

16:46.513 --> 16:47.849
in the world.

16:47.881 --> 16:49.650
So you want to throw us out?

16:49.684 --> 16:50.518
Oh, no.

16:52.653 --> 16:57.659
But perhaps you have something
that's worth selling.

16:58.892 --> 17:01.629
I have heard that you own
quite a special trinket.

17:02.830 --> 17:04.330
Small.

17:04.365 --> 17:05.333
Red.

17:07.001 --> 17:08.270
Pointy?

17:10.036 --> 17:14.340
That one can wear
around the neck?

17:15.608 --> 17:16.910
You mean the
fragment of blood?

17:21.348 --> 17:22.416
Where are you, dad?

17:24.017 --> 17:25.085
I'm sure he's still coming.

17:27.053 --> 17:29.990
You shouldn't miss the opening
speech Young Master Tepes?

17:32.726 --> 17:34.061
How do you know my name?

17:35.730 --> 17:37.966
It's my pleasure to meet
you, my name is Hannappel,

17:38.832 --> 17:40.567
and you really should go in now.

17:40.600 --> 17:42.070
Trust me, you don't
wanna miss it.

17:44.071 --> 17:46.907
(BROOM SQUEAKING)

17:46.940 --> 17:48.042
Hey, not you.

17:49.409 --> 17:50.044
Come back!

17:52.112 --> 17:53.914
Stop there, young lady.

17:55.382 --> 17:57.885
(ORGAN MUSIC)

18:02.689 --> 18:05.859
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

18:19.639 --> 18:21.042
My dear parents,

18:21.975 --> 18:23.911
my dear students.

18:26.580 --> 18:31.018
The number seven has
always been a magic number.

18:31.051 --> 18:33.987
Even the old alchemists
knew that seven

18:34.955 --> 18:37.524
is the number of new beginnings,

18:37.558 --> 18:41.396
of transition, of
transformation.

18:42.596 --> 18:44.732
It is not for nothing
that a new week begins

18:44.764 --> 18:45.999
after seven days.

18:47.134 --> 18:49.036
And like the seven
wonders of the world,

18:49.069 --> 18:53.040
we now have you,
our new year sevens.

18:53.072 --> 18:56.009
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

18:56.042 --> 18:59.013
More like the seventh horse.
(SNICKERING)

18:59.045 --> 19:01.581
Entry into the
seventh class marks

19:01.615 --> 19:06.621
the beginning of your own,
very own journey of experience.

19:08.656 --> 19:09.890
I saved a place for you.

19:10.925 --> 19:11.759
Your seventh school year...

19:11.792 --> 19:14.594
Comes late on the
first day, typical.

19:14.628 --> 19:18.532
In which you will take over
the legacy of your families.

19:20.000 --> 19:22.770
The blood fragment has been
family owned for generations.

19:22.802 --> 19:24.938
(WHOOSHING)

19:28.509 --> 19:29.176
Good morning.

19:31.244 --> 19:34.014
Is there a problem,
Ms. Circemeyer?

19:34.048 --> 19:38.085
Lord Mayor, yes,
well, there wouldn't be

19:38.118 --> 19:42.689
if Mr. Tepes here would
make a tiny sacrifice

19:42.723 --> 19:45.257
in order to stay
here in Crailsfelden.

19:45.259 --> 19:46.528
He owes taxes.

19:47.561 --> 19:48.196
I see.

19:49.964 --> 19:54.902
Well, first of all, welcome
to Crailsfelden, my good man.

19:54.935 --> 19:56.537
Good day, Lord Mayor.

19:56.570 --> 20:01.576
Relocation costs and new
acquisitions, welcome money.

20:02.109 --> 20:03.578
Welcome money, but...

20:03.610 --> 20:05.545
Yes, you have to
pay that as well.

20:05.579 --> 20:07.048
All these things cost money.

20:07.080 --> 20:10.484
I would be willing to
pay you a pretty penny

20:10.517 --> 20:11.785
for the blood fragment.

20:13.186 --> 20:17.023
And now I ask the students
of the year seven grade

20:17.057 --> 20:18.059
to come forward.

20:20.060 --> 20:21.662
Daniel Ussso.

20:21.695 --> 20:24.999
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

20:25.032 --> 20:26.000
Julia Astra.

20:30.070 --> 20:31.071
Barnt Ackebalt.

20:35.109 --> 20:38.879
Zirell Zari.
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

20:38.913 --> 20:39.881
Marie Utral.

20:41.814 --> 20:42.749
Wolf Vermin.

20:44.150 --> 20:47.554
(WOLF'S PARENTS HOWLING)

20:48.621 --> 20:49.823
Faye Lemayna.

20:52.626 --> 20:53.528
Urdin Vool.

20:56.263 --> 20:57.866
WOMAN: Urdini!

20:59.032 --> 21:01.569
HEADMISTRESS: Vlad Tepes.

21:04.338 --> 21:06.040
Karen Lazarus.

21:07.206 --> 21:09.810
Lord Mayor, even
if I wanted to,

21:09.842 --> 21:11.778
the blood fragment
belongs to my son.

21:12.679 --> 21:13.781
Is that so?

21:15.182 --> 21:18.219
That is, it once belonged
to my wife, my late wife

21:18.252 --> 21:19.052
and Vlad would never give it up.

21:19.086 --> 21:20.788
How moving.

21:20.821 --> 21:23.690
Please believe us, we are
grateful that you invited us

21:23.724 --> 21:25.192
to Crailsfelden and...

21:25.225 --> 21:28.862
But Mr. Tepes, there are more
important things than taxes.

21:28.896 --> 21:29.830
Yes.

21:29.862 --> 21:31.999
We'll find a way, my dear man.

21:33.100 --> 21:34.201
Thank you, Lord Mayor.

21:34.234 --> 21:35.235
I really have to
go now, thank you.

21:37.638 --> 21:38.239
Stop!

21:46.245 --> 21:48.983
The day after tomorrow,
the solar eclipse spectacle

21:49.015 --> 21:52.085
will take place on the
Crailsfelden Town Hall square.

21:52.953 --> 21:54.221
You should not miss that.

21:54.253 --> 21:56.057
Of course, Lord
Mayor, until then.

22:08.735 --> 22:10.271
(CAPE WHOOSHING)

22:10.303 --> 22:13.140
(MAGIC TWINKLING)

22:26.853 --> 22:29.990
My magic brings it to life.

22:32.359 --> 22:33.695
What is hidden,

22:35.795 --> 22:36.597
show your face.

22:37.865 --> 22:39.701
What is laid in
darkness for so long.

22:40.900 --> 22:43.837
The time has come,
trust the light.

22:44.838 --> 22:47.274
(EPIC MUSIC)

22:50.010 --> 22:51.045
What have I missed?

23:05.292 --> 23:06.360
Salamandra.

23:11.298 --> 23:12.300
Hey, cool!

23:13.434 --> 23:14.969
WOMAN: Verdi!

23:15.002 --> 23:17.938
(AUDIENCE GASPING)

23:23.877 --> 23:27.447
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

23:27.481 --> 23:28.316
Finally!

23:32.953 --> 23:35.123
You look great, darling!

23:40.127 --> 23:41.329
Look at that!

23:42.262 --> 23:45.399
(BLOWING RASPBERRIES)

23:49.069 --> 23:52.306
(WOLF SNARLING)

23:52.339 --> 23:54.175
HORST: Yes, Wolfie!

23:59.245 --> 24:00.247
My wolfie!

24:04.984 --> 24:07.254
(LAUGHING)

24:23.803 --> 24:25.138
That's my son.

24:28.175 --> 24:29.844
Bravo Vladdy, bravo.

24:33.312 --> 24:35.282
(SCREAMS) Oh
God, it's too high.

24:35.314 --> 24:36.917
I need to film this.

24:36.949 --> 24:38.018
Help, help!

24:39.253 --> 24:40.253
Get me down!

24:41.455 --> 24:43.824
(SNEEZING)

24:46.392 --> 24:48.762
(SCREAMS)

24:51.365 --> 24:52.200
Vladdy!

24:57.137 --> 24:59.106
(SNEEZING)

24:59.138 --> 25:00.306
Vladdy, are you okay?

25:00.340 --> 25:01.175
Are you hurt?

25:03.342 --> 25:04.311
(SNEEZING)

25:04.343 --> 25:06.846
Thank God you're okay.

25:06.879 --> 25:08.314
Are you all right?

25:08.348 --> 25:09.149
What's wrong?

25:10.317 --> 25:11.486
You're bleeding, did
you bite your lip?

25:13.920 --> 25:16.090
(RETCHES)

25:30.369 --> 25:32.773
And, are you feeling better?

25:33.940 --> 25:37.310
Oh, you got something.

25:39.580 --> 25:41.549
Vampire vomit.

25:41.581 --> 25:43.850
Dracula woulda
turned in his grave.

25:45.252 --> 25:47.989
Which wouldn't be easy,
with a wooden stake in his...

25:50.991 --> 25:53.327
You said, I'd become a proper
vampire in the year seven.

25:54.494 --> 25:55.929
And now I'm not
just the new guy,

25:55.963 --> 25:57.465
I'm the new freak,
the laughingstock.

25:58.631 --> 26:00.368
We should never
have come here.

26:01.534 --> 26:03.937
Vladdy, I know that
things didn't go the way

26:03.971 --> 26:06.207
we both wanted them to.

26:06.240 --> 26:09.443
But I'm sure everyone will
have forgotten by tomorrow.

26:09.475 --> 26:12.312
Forgotten that I'm a
vampire who can't stand blood?

26:13.480 --> 26:16.417
Vladdy, you know, once
your body has adjusted to it,

26:16.449 --> 26:18.051
then it will come naturally.

26:18.084 --> 26:20.453
And until then
we'll ease you in,

26:20.486 --> 26:23.122
a glass of blood orange
juice in the morning

26:23.156 --> 26:24.959
and a fresh juicy
steak at lunchtime.

26:24.992 --> 26:27.461
And then, and a slice
of lemon pudding...

26:27.494 --> 26:29.196
(VLAD RETCHING)

26:29.228 --> 26:31.164
HORST: What, allergic to fur?

26:32.498 --> 26:34.133
Yes, it's very common.

26:34.167 --> 26:35.069
Not so, don't worry about it.

26:35.101 --> 26:37.370
Don't worry, don't worry?

26:38.571 --> 26:41.908
We are werewolves, and
I am the pack leader.

26:41.942 --> 26:44.345
What will the others
think when they hear that?

26:44.378 --> 26:46.480
They'll laugh their fur off.

26:46.513 --> 26:48.148
Yes, well, I'll be off now

26:48.180 --> 26:49.482
and drink lots of electrolytes.

26:49.515 --> 26:50.551
Thank you, goodbye.

26:52.519 --> 26:53.554
Horst!

27:16.342 --> 27:19.412
Vladdy, I know that all
of this is not easy for you.

27:19.446 --> 27:21.348
But you will do it, I know that.

27:21.380 --> 27:23.484
Please believe me,
everything will get better.

27:25.252 --> 27:27.421
I'll just take this away.

27:36.663 --> 27:40.100
Maybe we could try
aromatherapy or...

27:40.132 --> 27:43.603
That son of Herman's
tore apart his first rabbit

27:43.637 --> 27:44.938
in year seven.

27:46.305 --> 27:49.342
My son, he has a
fur allergy (ROARS).

27:50.409 --> 27:52.412
Horst, how about homeopathy?

27:54.046 --> 27:58.685
HORST: Homeopathy, herbal
remedies, don't make me sick!

28:07.194 --> 28:09.430
(SNIFFLES)

28:14.467 --> 28:16.637
(SOBBING)

28:36.356 --> 28:39.093
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

28:49.202 --> 28:51.372
(CRASHES)

28:54.541 --> 28:57.043
(CAT MEWLING)

28:59.413 --> 29:00.247
Vlad?

29:02.549 --> 29:05.519
(TRASH CANS RATTLING)

29:40.753 --> 29:44.058
(CIRCEMEYER HUMMING)

30:15.288 --> 30:17.391
(GROANS)

30:49.488 --> 30:52.158
(PLAYFUL MUSIC)

31:36.669 --> 31:39.806
(CIRCEMEYER CRASHING)

31:50.850 --> 31:52.520
Do you have the fragment?

31:56.956 --> 31:58.691
I'm fine, thanks for asking.

31:58.725 --> 31:59.560
The fragment!

32:16.309 --> 32:16.944
Finally.

32:19.846 --> 32:20.847
No!

32:20.879 --> 32:23.216
What's happened?

32:23.250 --> 32:25.452
It's a recall spell.

32:25.484 --> 32:26.286
A what?

32:29.822 --> 32:34.393
The blood fragment is
secured by a recall spell.

32:34.426 --> 32:37.697
It can only change
hands if it is given up

32:37.731 --> 32:39.400
of its own free will.

32:51.410 --> 32:52.745
It's almost like it's cursed.

32:59.753 --> 33:01.388
GIRL: There's
the crash pilot.

33:22.876 --> 33:24.445
He's bleeding to death, help!

33:26.012 --> 33:31.018
GIRL: Oh my
God, so much blood.

33:33.953 --> 33:35.923
(RETCHES)

33:39.458 --> 33:41.262
He really bought it.

33:42.594 --> 33:43.896
Vlad, are you all right?

33:46.433 --> 33:48.502
You should really be
ashamed of yourself.

33:49.903 --> 33:51.938
One would think that a
shapeshifter, a night elf

33:51.971 --> 33:53.373
and a sorcerer's apprentice

33:53.406 --> 33:55.042
would do better
with their powers.

33:58.844 --> 34:00.947
Someone should clean
that up (SNICKERS).

34:04.516 --> 34:05.652
You get started.

34:41.020 --> 34:42.956
What are you doing here?

34:42.989 --> 34:45.359
I wanna get out
of here, you too?

34:45.391 --> 34:47.527
No, I thought
today is hiking day

34:47.560 --> 34:49.730
and I made a mistake
with the date.

34:49.763 --> 34:50.996
Oh, all right.

34:51.029 --> 34:53.833
Sorry, wasn't meant like that.

34:53.866 --> 34:58.504
But I can no longer be
seen in Crailsfelden.

34:58.538 --> 35:01.007
(WOLF SNEEZING)

35:02.074 --> 35:03.643
What are you doing here?

35:05.944 --> 35:07.046
WOLF: I hate the woods.

35:07.080 --> 35:08.047
Are you okay?

35:10.850 --> 35:13.018
Are you running away too?

35:13.052 --> 35:15.922
I want to go out into the
world, experience adventure

35:15.955 --> 35:17.924
and defy danger so
that my father can see

35:17.956 --> 35:19.993
I'm a real wolf man.

35:20.025 --> 35:21.895
With a Theo Tiger backpack?

35:21.927 --> 35:23.429
Yes, why?

35:23.462 --> 35:26.366
All right, then
let's get out of here.

35:29.601 --> 35:30.737
It's a cool backpack.

35:45.051 --> 35:47.987
Okay, if we want to
experience adventures together

35:48.020 --> 35:52.058
then you don't have to be
afraid, you have me (SCREAMS)

35:52.991 --> 35:54.460
Who goes here?

35:56.929 --> 35:58.866
Let us just go through, okay?

36:00.065 --> 36:04.203
You can't go, you cannot leave

36:04.237 --> 36:07.741
until what is written in
the book is fulfilled.

36:07.773 --> 36:10.844
Huh?

36:14.147 --> 36:19.152
When time turns backwards and
calamity is high in the sky,

36:21.020 --> 36:26.025
one will come, and three will
unite into silent heroes,

36:28.862 --> 36:32.800
who wrest the devil's
fate from Crailsfelden.

36:35.101 --> 36:37.204
I don't care what it
says, I'm outta here.

36:37.237 --> 36:38.839
Don't make me angry.

36:40.038 --> 36:42.743
You wouldn't like
me when I'm angry.

36:45.844 --> 36:47.147
I don't like you now either.

36:48.514 --> 36:53.085
Okay, Quasimodo, you
let us pass or we'll...

36:54.920 --> 36:56.989
(GROANING)

37:07.866 --> 37:12.171
Okay, and what if we say
we're really, really sorry?

37:13.139 --> 37:17.077
You, are, staying, here.

37:20.647 --> 37:22.915
Leave the children alone.

37:25.618 --> 37:26.253
Kids, come on.

37:28.121 --> 37:30.724
I want to exercise the horror.

37:30.757 --> 37:33.159
What now has a wicked
eye, lose your evil,

37:33.192 --> 37:35.795
by and by, salamandra!

37:35.828 --> 37:38.665
(MAGIC TWINKLING)

37:39.331 --> 37:40.567
Okay, wrong spell, don't panic.

37:40.600 --> 37:42.868
Wrong spell, don't panic.

37:42.902 --> 37:44.271
Wrong spell, stay calm.

37:44.304 --> 37:45.138
Stay calm.

37:50.109 --> 37:52.679
(BRUCKENTROLL GROANS)

37:52.712 --> 37:53.647
Salt, always helps
against demons.

37:53.679 --> 37:54.514
Come on, run!

37:56.348 --> 37:58.684
He shouldn't have done that.

37:58.717 --> 38:01.254
I didn't mean it
that way (SOBBING).

38:08.761 --> 38:11.898
I didn't know you were
a wizard, Mr. Hannappel.

38:11.931 --> 38:14.100
Well, I'm not allowed to
do magic at school anymore

38:14.132 --> 38:16.268
since I helped with the staging
of the flying classroom,

38:16.302 --> 38:19.139
but nevermind, almost everyone
made it back down there.

38:19.172 --> 38:20.273
Someone else green?

38:21.139 --> 38:23.143
Yes, Salamandra.

38:24.844 --> 38:26.313
(MAGIC TWINKLING)

38:26.346 --> 38:30.183
So kids, tell me why you
wanted to leave Crailsfelden.

38:30.215 --> 38:32.319
I mean a vampire
who can't see blood,

38:32.351 --> 38:34.087
an elf with a fear of flying,

38:34.119 --> 38:36.121
and a werewolf with
an animal air allergy,

38:36.154 --> 38:37.823
it's very unusual.

38:37.857 --> 38:41.226
But running away is
not a solution, is it?

38:41.259 --> 38:43.862
Yeah, but we can't
stay here either.

38:43.895 --> 38:46.065
There must be another
way than this bridge.

38:46.098 --> 38:49.201
No, you can only get in
and out over the bridge.

38:49.235 --> 38:52.172
Crailsfelden is surrounded
by a magical forest.

38:52.205 --> 38:53.840
You could go through it for days

38:53.873 --> 38:55.708
and you would always come
out in the same place

38:55.741 --> 38:58.110
where you started, but
it's strange somehow.

38:58.143 --> 39:00.946
The bridge guard only pays
attention to who wants to enter.

39:00.980 --> 39:02.248
Everyone can get out.

39:02.281 --> 39:04.016
Then why not us too?

39:04.049 --> 39:04.817
Good question.

39:06.219 --> 39:08.355
Perhaps there is
something about it in

39:08.388 --> 39:12.692
"Strange Customs and Creepy
Customs of Crailsfelden Vol. 13"

39:12.725 --> 39:15.295
page 777, salamandra!

39:16.261 --> 39:19.732
(BOOKS HIT THE GROUND)

39:25.038 --> 39:26.106
Hmm, let's see.

39:26.139 --> 39:28.041
So here.

39:29.308 --> 39:31.878
Ah, mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

39:34.447 --> 39:35.282
Ah.

39:38.284 --> 39:41.855
(GASPS) No, it is not in it.

39:43.456 --> 39:44.725
More hot chocolate?

39:46.159 --> 39:47.060
No thanks.

39:47.092 --> 39:49.328
Yes, yes me please.

40:08.714 --> 40:12.017
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)
forbidden library,

40:12.051 --> 40:14.286
beyond the abyss of ignorance.

40:14.319 --> 40:15.187
(SPEAKING FOREIGN
LANGUAGE) what?

40:15.221 --> 40:16.889
It's Latin.

40:16.922 --> 40:19.692
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE),
the book of all knowledge?

40:19.726 --> 40:21.394
HANNAPPEL: Do you
like cream on top?

40:21.427 --> 40:23.063
Yes, yes please.

40:23.096 --> 40:25.165
HANNAPPEL: Coming
right up, salamandra!

40:27.333 --> 40:28.869
Does ketchup work too?

40:30.069 --> 40:31.804
Is it lactose free too?

40:31.837 --> 40:32.906
I'm allergic.

40:32.938 --> 40:33.873
HANNAPPEL: Sorry?

40:33.906 --> 40:35.308
With a little bit of cinnamon?

40:35.340 --> 40:37.476
HANNAPPEL: Yes, of
course, no problem.

40:37.509 --> 40:41.214
It also says with the prophecy
of that stupid troll means

40:41.246 --> 40:42.781
and if we can fulfill them,

40:42.815 --> 40:44.951
then we would be the
heroes of Crailsfelden

40:44.984 --> 40:46.853
and my dad would admire me.

40:47.987 --> 40:49.189
Above all, the troll
would let us out.

40:49.221 --> 40:51.824
HANNAPPEL: I will be
right there, salamandra!

40:53.058 --> 40:57.096
(SCREAMING) Spiders,
I hate spiders!

40:57.130 --> 40:58.264
So where's this book?

40:58.297 --> 41:00.833
It says here in the
forbidden library.

41:00.866 --> 41:04.303
HANNAPPEL: All right
now, cocoa is coming.

41:04.337 --> 41:05.371
I know where it is.

41:11.344 --> 41:13.413
Children, it is
quite late now.

41:13.446 --> 41:15.748
I think you'd better
go home, right?

41:15.781 --> 41:18.217
In any case, I should
put out the kitchen.

41:18.250 --> 41:20.753
You're quite
right, Mr. Hannappel.

41:20.786 --> 41:21.788
You've been a great help.

41:21.821 --> 41:23.123
Oh, really?

41:23.156 --> 41:25.826
That's nice, I'm
happy to hear that.

41:40.139 --> 41:41.941
Wolf, everything okay?

41:41.973 --> 41:44.310
Yes, just all these trees.

41:45.478 --> 41:47.413
I always have to, you know,
raise a leg and stuff.

41:47.446 --> 41:49.382
You're not serious, are you?

41:49.415 --> 41:51.051
No, no, tricked you.

41:57.123 --> 41:57.958
Hang on.

42:04.897 --> 42:06.833
VLAD: What was that?

42:06.866 --> 42:09.902
Elven dust has healing powers.

42:09.935 --> 42:11.837
This is really
your thing, isn't it?

42:12.605 --> 42:16.074
Elves help, remember?

42:16.107 --> 42:17.443
I've never met an elf.

42:19.045 --> 42:21.147
I grew up among people.

42:21.179 --> 42:23.817
Until I was four, I didn't
even know I was a vampire.

42:24.851 --> 42:25.819
And your mother?

42:29.188 --> 42:31.458
My mother, she
died in an accident.

42:32.491 --> 42:34.594
I can hardly remember her.

42:34.627 --> 42:36.862
This is all I've got from her.

42:36.895 --> 42:38.497
It's a magical crystal, right?

42:39.431 --> 42:41.500
Is it under a recall spell?

42:41.534 --> 42:43.302
How do you know that?

42:43.335 --> 42:46.038
I know a little bit
about crystal magic.

42:46.072 --> 42:48.441
I actually wanted to
study that later but...

42:48.473 --> 42:51.277
(WOLF PANTING)

43:08.194 --> 43:09.029
Now!

43:17.235 --> 43:18.071
There.

43:55.975 --> 43:56.610
A map!

43:58.009 --> 44:01.446
Let's see, so we are here.

44:01.480 --> 44:03.215
Where do we have to go now?

44:06.985 --> 44:10.489
Liber omnis scientia,
the book of all knowledge.

44:10.522 --> 44:11.457
Shelf 313.

44:14.493 --> 44:15.561
I think we have
to go through here.

44:15.594 --> 44:17.030
Ah, guys?

44:17.063 --> 44:18.932
VLAD: Then just
straight ahead.

44:18.964 --> 44:21.033
Can you give me a hand?

44:21.067 --> 44:22.268
Do you think
they'll just let us...

44:22.301 --> 44:24.636
(WOLF SNARLS)

44:24.670 --> 44:27.072
Okay, I withdraw the question.

44:27.105 --> 44:29.508
I'll distract him, I'm
looking for a book, okay?

44:29.542 --> 44:32.411
(WOLF SNARLING)

44:44.522 --> 44:45.991
Nice treats.

44:46.025 --> 44:47.961
VLAD: Why have you
got those with you?

44:47.993 --> 44:49.261
It's my lunch.

44:53.431 --> 44:54.667
Should we make friends first?

44:59.038 --> 45:01.507
(WOLF SNIFFING)

45:28.366 --> 45:29.167
(FAYE SCREAMS)

45:29.201 --> 45:30.036
Faye!

45:33.605 --> 45:36.542
(FOREBODING MUSIC)

45:40.078 --> 45:42.081
Beyond the abyss of ignorance.

45:42.748 --> 45:45.018
How should we get over it?

45:45.051 --> 45:45.717
Fly?

45:45.750 --> 45:48.620
No way, forget it.

45:48.654 --> 45:51.090
The library is over there.

45:51.123 --> 45:54.659
I guess it just serves
to overcome ignorance.

45:54.692 --> 45:57.096
This is definitely just
an optical illusion.

45:58.431 --> 45:59.232
Watch out.

46:08.808 --> 46:10.342
Pretty good illusion.

46:12.710 --> 46:15.547
(BATS SCREECHING)

46:19.485 --> 46:20.453
Friends of yours?

46:24.857 --> 46:27.627
The Nosferatu sensor.

46:27.659 --> 46:30.228
I know Nosferatu, but...

46:30.261 --> 46:32.597
The bats, they have
this built-in radar.

46:32.630 --> 46:34.634
With ultrasound, and?

46:34.667 --> 46:37.469
Maybe I can now too,
but you can't laugh.

46:44.176 --> 46:48.480
(MIMICKING BAT SCREECHES)

46:48.514 --> 46:51.084
(FAYE GIGGLES)

47:01.594 --> 47:02.662
Did you see anything?

47:02.694 --> 47:05.730
There are pillars,
invisible pillars?

47:05.764 --> 47:08.701
We can make it but
we have to jump.

47:12.304 --> 47:13.139
Come on.

47:13.772 --> 47:14.607
You can do it

47:17.243 --> 47:19.277
we'll jump together,
you just hold on tight

47:19.310 --> 47:20.513
and close your eyes.

47:21.679 --> 47:24.449
Do you remember
where the pillars are?

47:24.482 --> 47:26.351
Yeah, sure.

47:26.384 --> 47:28.087
More or less.

47:28.786 --> 47:30.255
Yeah, trust me, okay.

47:30.288 --> 47:31.623
On three.

47:31.656 --> 47:33.192
One, two, three.

47:39.331 --> 47:41.234
The next one was there?

47:42.902 --> 47:43.735
Or to the right?

47:43.768 --> 47:45.203
Vlad?

47:45.237 --> 47:47.339
Yeah, yeah, it's all
good, I remember now.

47:51.210 --> 47:51.845
Three.

47:56.181 --> 47:57.516
Thank you.

47:57.549 --> 47:58.618
Elves help.

48:03.755 --> 48:04.857
Two, three.

48:06.525 --> 48:07.327
We did it!

48:14.766 --> 48:15.835
Okay, Headmistress.

48:16.835 --> 48:18.571
I'll discuss it with him.

48:18.603 --> 48:20.272
No, that's unusual for me too...

48:20.306 --> 48:22.775
(CIRCEMEYER CRASHES)

48:22.808 --> 48:25.844
Thank you for the call,
goodbye Headmistress.

48:30.815 --> 48:33.485
(BELL DINGING)

48:33.518 --> 48:35.854
Ms. Cercemeyer, I
was just about...

48:35.888 --> 48:40.893
My dear Mr. Tepes, Barnabus.

48:42.560 --> 48:45.564
Wouldn't it be a shame if
you and your little Vladdy

48:45.598 --> 48:47.667
had to leave Crailsfelden?

48:47.699 --> 48:48.902
Well, yes.

48:50.835 --> 48:52.906
(GROANING)

48:56.442 --> 49:00.413
Now, if you could
convince your son

49:00.446 --> 49:03.183
to sell the blood fragment,

49:04.382 --> 49:08.420
then you could stay here
in Crailsfelden forever.

49:10.556 --> 49:11.391
With me.

49:12.958 --> 49:15.795
I will speak to
him about it as soon

49:15.828 --> 49:17.429
as I know where he is.

49:18.697 --> 49:19.965
What?

49:19.998 --> 49:23.301
Well, he ran away from
school and I was just about

49:23.335 --> 49:24.804
to go looking for him.

49:24.837 --> 49:29.775
But in the meantime, I might
interest you in something else.

49:29.808 --> 49:34.547
For example here, the original
Barbarossa beard trimmer,

49:34.580 --> 49:39.252
a unique piece, perfect for
unisex bewitching haircuts.

49:40.786 --> 49:41.721
Cercemeyer?

49:55.768 --> 49:56.869
Wow, crazy.

50:22.094 --> 50:22.895
I knew it.

50:25.630 --> 50:27.699
It's not all that high.

50:31.969 --> 50:33.872
And when you're flying high,

50:33.906 --> 50:35.507
just close your eyes
and I'll direct you.

50:35.540 --> 50:36.908
Like a remote control or what?

50:45.984 --> 50:46.985
Can I try?

50:49.654 --> 50:50.857
Mmh, tasty?

50:52.523 --> 50:55.627
No, no, Okay, today is Dog Day.

50:55.661 --> 50:56.863
Left, more to the left.

50:58.529 --> 51:00.732
Just a little bit higher.

51:00.766 --> 51:02.968
Still higher?

51:03.000 --> 51:04.569
I'm afraid so, yeah.

51:07.973 --> 51:11.944
Guys, I'm almost
out of treats here.

51:11.976 --> 51:14.547
(WOLF WHINING)

51:16.081 --> 51:17.483
You're nearly there.

51:18.951 --> 51:20.753
Now all you have
to do is reach out.

51:22.020 --> 51:23.355
A little higher.

51:25.623 --> 51:26.426
Now!

51:33.565 --> 51:35.034
Have you got it?

51:36.000 --> 51:38.470
VLAD: Yeah, I
caught it with my face.

51:38.503 --> 51:40.373
You must be full
by now, right?

51:42.507 --> 51:43.975
I don't have anymore left.

51:44.009 --> 51:46.878
(WOLF SNARLING)

51:49.982 --> 51:50.983
Am I down yet?

51:51.016 --> 51:51.918
Can I open my eyes now?

51:53.618 --> 51:55.887
Yeah, you were great.

51:56.989 --> 51:58.925
I hate to rush you, but...

52:00.625 --> 52:01.993
Guys?

52:02.027 --> 52:04.130
Take it easy, take it real easy.

52:04.163 --> 52:07.065
It's all good, good boy.

52:07.098 --> 52:08.900
What took you guys so long?

52:08.933 --> 52:10.602
Got the book, bye.

52:12.438 --> 52:15.608
(KIDS SCREAMING)

52:15.641 --> 52:18.110
(WOLF SNARLING)

52:25.150 --> 52:26.853
Everything okay?

52:28.686 --> 52:30.123
Wolf, you didn't
sneeze at all.

52:32.023 --> 52:33.025
Right.

52:34.592 --> 52:35.860
(SNEEZES)

52:35.893 --> 52:37.729
What do you mean
he's not at home?

52:37.763 --> 52:39.065
Find him!

52:41.600 --> 52:43.069
I need the fragment.

52:49.741 --> 52:50.576
One moment.

52:51.944 --> 52:53.746
There's no reception here.

52:53.779 --> 52:54.647
No witch-fi.

53:01.619 --> 53:05.056
There he is, with two
other snotty brats.

53:06.525 --> 53:09.962
What do they have there?

53:09.994 --> 53:12.031
That is the Liber
Omnis Scientia.

53:12.063 --> 53:13.199
(MIRROR BREAKS)

53:13.232 --> 53:16.002
How the hell did they get that?

53:17.802 --> 53:19.971
That was the latest model.

53:33.685 --> 53:36.956
Cool, it's like
a built-in browser.

53:36.989 --> 53:39.525
NARRATOR: Be warned, readers,

53:39.558 --> 53:42.161
because there is one
among us who cannot stand

53:42.194 --> 53:45.965
that the magical beings have
become peaceful creatures.

53:45.998 --> 53:49.068
Lord Lucifer, The Terrible.

53:49.101 --> 53:52.003
(GASPS) I mean, wow.

53:53.237 --> 53:55.674
NARRATOR: The Prince of
Darkness has only one goal.

53:55.706 --> 54:00.145
He wants to go back in
time so that all vampires,

54:00.177 --> 54:03.715
all werewolves, and all
other creatures of the night

54:03.748 --> 54:07.219
become the evil monsters
they were once again.

54:08.786 --> 54:12.524
As his army of darkness,
they're supposed to take back

54:12.558 --> 54:14.927
the world of men for him.

54:14.960 --> 54:17.830
So know this and shiver.

54:17.862 --> 54:20.866
At the 13th hour when...

54:23.101 --> 54:24.069
When What?

54:24.101 --> 54:26.739
Someone tore
out the last page.

54:29.074 --> 54:33.212
I made sure centuries
ago that nobody found out

54:33.244 --> 54:36.080
too much from that damn book.

54:36.114 --> 54:37.081
Then everything is fine.

54:37.114 --> 54:38.283
Nothing is fine!

54:39.951 --> 54:43.855
When these brats warn the
residents of Crailsfelden.

54:43.889 --> 54:45.124
That won't happen.

54:56.201 --> 54:57.802
(VLAD COUGHING)

54:57.835 --> 55:02.841
Okay, at the 13th hour,
Lucifer will do something

55:06.143 --> 55:08.113
to make all of the
magical creatures evil.

55:10.815 --> 55:12.083
But what?

55:12.116 --> 55:14.752
But what, there's
no 13th hour.

55:14.786 --> 55:17.923
Well apparently,
and then he will turn

55:17.956 --> 55:21.327
all Crailsfelden residents
back into monsters

55:21.360 --> 55:22.929
and enslave them.

55:24.161 --> 55:26.031
(SIGHS) Which ointment?

55:26.063 --> 55:29.167
Flying spell, shrinking powder.

55:33.105 --> 55:36.375
There you are.

55:36.407 --> 55:38.578
Reverse curse (GIGGLES).

55:45.217 --> 55:47.619
Have fun, my little one.

55:49.221 --> 55:53.025
Turn their words
around in their mouths.

55:54.426 --> 55:56.328
We have to tell
our parents for sure.

55:56.360 --> 55:58.196
And then we'll call
each other, okay?

55:58.230 --> 55:59.098
That's a deal.

56:08.206 --> 56:10.943
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

56:22.119 --> 56:24.357
(FAYE GASPS)

56:27.759 --> 56:28.460
Dad, dad!

56:32.330 --> 56:34.366
Vladdy, my boy, there you are.

56:34.398 --> 56:35.400
Is everything okay?

56:35.433 --> 56:37.368
Yeah, all good.

56:37.402 --> 56:39.271
Oh, that's great,
I was quite worried.

56:39.304 --> 56:40.873
But why?

56:40.906 --> 56:42.940
Th re's no reason for that,
nothing bad ever happens here.

56:42.973 --> 56:47.013
True, Vladdy, the thing is,

56:49.081 --> 56:52.985
Ms. Cercemeyer, the assistant
to Lord Mayor Ziffer

56:53.018 --> 56:57.389
was here earlier, and she is
quite willing to pay a nice sum

56:57.422 --> 56:59.692
for your blood fragment there.

56:59.725 --> 57:01.027
Okay, that's great!

57:02.493 --> 57:04.328
Vladdy, before
you say anything,

57:04.362 --> 57:05.764
I know it means a lot to you.

57:05.797 --> 57:08.199
It is after all a memory
of your mother but...

57:10.235 --> 57:12.237
Did you just say great?

57:12.270 --> 57:13.739
Yeah!

57:13.772 --> 57:15.708
Vladdy, I'm so glad that
you see it the same way.

57:15.741 --> 57:17.208
Vladdy, if we sell
the blood fragment,

57:17.241 --> 57:19.243
you can go to
school and I can...

57:19.277 --> 57:20.311
Vladdy?

57:24.415 --> 57:26.118
Vlad, can I come in?

57:26.150 --> 57:27.319
Yes, sure.

57:31.223 --> 57:32.791
Vlad, what's wrong, my boy?

57:32.824 --> 57:34.226
We can always talk
about anything.

57:34.259 --> 57:36.929
I know, dad, I'm
telling you how I feel.

57:38.295 --> 57:41.232
Ms. Cercemeyer is a
really, really nice woman.

57:41.266 --> 57:43.402
And doesn't she
have a lovely nose.

57:43.435 --> 57:45.471
Vladdy, wouldn't you like
to meet her sometime?

57:45.503 --> 57:47.371
For sure, I have
absolutely nothing else

57:47.404 --> 57:48.306
going on right now.

57:48.339 --> 57:49.941
Oh, I'm happy to hear that.

57:49.975 --> 57:52.877
Vladdy, how about tomorrow
morning in front of the school.

57:52.911 --> 57:54.480
You could accompany
me to the town hall

57:54.513 --> 57:56.281
when I want to sell
her the blood fragment.

57:56.313 --> 57:58.250
Wouldn't you like
to give it to me now

57:58.282 --> 57:59.384
then I can polish it a little,

57:59.417 --> 58:01.219
put it in a nice
jewelry box with a bow.

58:01.252 --> 58:02.420
Sounds good.

58:06.257 --> 58:09.393
(SIGHS) Maybe I was the
same when I was a teenager,

58:09.427 --> 58:10.930
300 years ago.

58:24.141 --> 58:26.043
Guys, you won't believe
what just happened.

58:26.076 --> 58:29.413
Let me guess, you wanted
to warn your father.

58:29.447 --> 58:31.282
But it came out
the exact opposite

58:31.315 --> 58:32.317
of what you wanted to say?

58:32.350 --> 58:33.217
Me too.

58:33.250 --> 58:35.286
I was talking such
nonsense that my mother

58:35.319 --> 58:37.421
wanted to call Dr.
Frankenberg again.

58:37.455 --> 58:40.292
He just didn't come because
dad bit him last time.

58:40.324 --> 58:41.960
It's called a reverse curse.

58:41.993 --> 58:45.964
I looked it up, pretty bad
black magic and totally illegal.

58:45.996 --> 58:47.465
It makes us say the opposite

58:47.498 --> 58:49.368
of what we actually
want to say to others.

58:49.400 --> 58:51.435
But we're all
talking normally now.

58:51.469 --> 58:54.005
Because all three of
us were hit by the curse.

58:54.038 --> 58:56.274
Okay, that means we have
to find out for ourselves

58:56.308 --> 58:58.277
what Lucifer is up to.

58:58.310 --> 58:59.844
I'll check out the book again.

58:59.877 --> 59:01.312
Maybe there's something else.

59:01.346 --> 59:05.284
Okay, and I'll look into
the thing about the 13th hour.

59:05.317 --> 59:08.219
And I'll find out how
magical beings turn vicious.

59:08.252 --> 59:10.054
Okay, meeting point
tomorrow morning

59:10.087 --> 59:11.389
at 8:00 at the fountain.

59:11.422 --> 59:12.924
WOLF: Okay, until tomorrow.

59:21.398 --> 59:24.036
But he was not
blessed with heirs,

59:24.069 --> 59:28.340
so Alfred the Angry was
succeeded by Crailsbirth III.

59:28.373 --> 59:31.443
In the year 1312,
Elrune Vongurtzer

59:31.476 --> 59:36.014
completed his famous
(YAWNS) filled it

59:36.047 --> 59:40.418
on the 17th of
March 1455 at 11:37.

59:40.451 --> 59:43.855
The date of 23 May
of the year 1845

59:43.889 --> 59:48.493
was the most uneventful day
in Crailsfelden's history.

59:48.525 --> 59:51.062
Around 4 p.m. light
drizzle set in,

59:51.096 --> 59:53.098
while at the same time,

59:53.130 --> 59:55.333
a sack of coal fell
over in the (MUMBLES).

01:00:00.572 --> 01:00:03.409
(ROOSTER CROWING)

01:00:28.098 --> 01:00:32.003
(BELL RINGING IN THE DISTANCE)

01:00:33.203 --> 01:00:36.574
When Crailsfelden's
Town Hall strikes 13,

01:00:36.607 --> 01:00:40.444
the world as you know
it, will cease to be.

01:00:40.478 --> 01:00:43.081
When time turns backwards.

01:00:44.382 --> 01:00:45.617
Do you think
that's funny, boy?

01:00:45.650 --> 01:00:48.520
BRUCKENTROLL: And
calamity is high in the sky.

01:00:48.552 --> 01:00:49.955
(CYCLIST SCREAMING)

01:00:49.987 --> 01:00:50.955
CYCLIST: My
bike's been turned

01:00:50.989 --> 01:00:53.225
into this old Penny-farthing.

01:00:53.257 --> 01:00:54.092
The time!

01:00:59.197 --> 01:01:02.301
Vlad, this 13th hour,
it's from an old poem

01:01:02.333 --> 01:01:03.935
about the town hall.

01:01:03.969 --> 01:01:07.339
By Elron Vongertz,
ode to Crailsfelden

01:01:07.371 --> 01:01:10.375
written on the
17th of March 1455.

01:01:10.407 --> 01:01:12.110
Believe me, I've
read all about it.

01:01:12.143 --> 01:01:14.246
And I've only found one way

01:01:14.279 --> 01:01:16.514
to make night creatures
vicious again.

01:01:16.547 --> 01:01:18.549
Only with a dark crystal magic...

01:01:18.583 --> 01:01:19.485
Turns back time.

01:01:20.618 --> 01:01:22.688
When I arrived here
with my father,

01:01:22.721 --> 01:01:25.090
my blood fragment
started to glow,

01:01:25.123 --> 01:01:27.259
just as we drove past Town Hall.

01:01:27.292 --> 01:01:31.063
And at the same moment,
things went back in time.

01:01:31.096 --> 01:01:32.097
At the town hall?

01:01:33.531 --> 01:01:37.036
When the town hall strikes
13, the world will end.

01:01:38.469 --> 01:01:42.139
In any case, this time
magic has something to do

01:01:42.172 --> 01:01:43.375
with my blood fragment.

01:01:43.407 --> 01:01:45.310
Nothing against
your crystal, Vlad,

01:01:45.342 --> 01:01:48.446
but it's far from large enough
for such a powerful spell.

01:01:49.647 --> 01:01:50.581
Unless if...

01:01:50.614 --> 01:01:52.350
Something makes it stronger!

01:02:05.496 --> 01:02:07.532
Her photos are awesome.

01:02:11.469 --> 01:02:13.505
My phone, my brand new phone,

01:02:13.538 --> 01:02:15.706
it's a totally old one.

01:02:15.739 --> 01:02:16.774
GIRL: Ew, get rid of it!

01:02:16.808 --> 01:02:19.445
A time spell, definitely.

01:02:20.712 --> 01:02:22.347
Come on!

01:02:22.380 --> 01:02:26.552
Wait, it's school today,
and we're skipping it.

01:02:27.485 --> 01:02:28.220
What about Schnappauf?

01:02:29.453 --> 01:02:31.756
That's right, we forgot
about the constable.

01:02:31.790 --> 01:02:33.725
Vlad, you distract Schnappauf.

01:02:33.757 --> 01:02:35.460
I'll climb through a window,

01:02:35.493 --> 01:02:37.596
crawl through the ventilation
shafts, get into the town...

01:02:37.628 --> 01:02:40.398
That's a great idea, but
I think I have a better way.

01:02:40.431 --> 01:02:42.299
You know, vampires
have no reflection

01:02:42.333 --> 01:02:44.503
and therefore cannot be filmed.

01:02:44.536 --> 01:02:47.039
You just have to distract him.

01:02:53.511 --> 01:02:55.781
What do you want here?

01:02:55.813 --> 01:02:58.149
Hello, today is a school trip

01:02:58.183 --> 01:03:00.652
with a visit to the town hall,
we're just a little early.

01:03:00.685 --> 01:03:02.721
I don't know
anything about it.

01:03:02.753 --> 01:03:06.058
Your teacher should report it
to me and you wait outside.

01:03:09.661 --> 01:03:11.229
FAYE: Have you ever noticed

01:03:11.261 --> 01:03:13.731
that your monitors display
everything upside down?

01:03:15.366 --> 01:03:16.201
What?

01:03:17.634 --> 01:03:20.738
When I wave, you see my
left hand and not my right.

01:03:20.772 --> 01:03:23.340
Of course I see
your left hand.

01:03:23.373 --> 01:03:25.843
Well, from my perspective,
from my point of view,

01:03:25.877 --> 01:03:29.148
it is your right one
and on the monitor...

01:03:32.250 --> 01:03:33.152
It doesn't matter.

01:03:34.185 --> 01:03:35.654
Get lost.

01:03:35.686 --> 01:03:37.455
You're so clever.

01:03:38.623 --> 01:03:39.657
Cheers.

01:04:01.212 --> 01:04:02.647
Wolf.

01:04:02.679 --> 01:04:04.715
This is wolf den to bat
cave, have you seen anything?

01:04:04.748 --> 01:04:07.185
No, but there are zombies.

01:04:07.217 --> 01:04:08.719
I read about that.

01:04:08.752 --> 01:04:11.188
The city has to save,
so they replaced

01:04:11.221 --> 01:04:12.690
the officers with zombies.

01:04:12.723 --> 01:04:14.825
They work just as
quickly, cost nothing

01:04:14.859 --> 01:04:16.728
and nobody notices
the difference.

01:04:16.761 --> 01:04:18.496
So don't worry,
they're harmless.

01:04:19.429 --> 01:04:22.399
My crystal's going crazy.

01:04:22.433 --> 01:04:23.701
Be careful.

01:04:23.735 --> 01:04:27.539
I think the crystal is
being drawn to the tower.

01:04:39.449 --> 01:04:40.284
Hmm.

01:04:55.532 --> 01:04:56.835
Vlad, where are you now?

01:05:01.806 --> 01:05:02.840
I'm in the tower.

01:05:02.873 --> 01:05:04.743
WOLF: What is
it, what do you see?

01:05:10.514 --> 01:05:12.817
There's a huge crystal here.

01:05:14.786 --> 01:05:19.525
(KEYS CLACKING)
(YELPS)

01:05:33.371 --> 01:05:34.206
Ow!

01:05:37.775 --> 01:05:39.177
A time spell.

01:05:41.846 --> 01:05:42.813
Boss!

01:05:48.485 --> 01:05:49.119
No!

01:05:52.022 --> 01:05:54.257
FAYE: Vlad, Vlad, what is it?

01:05:54.259 --> 01:05:57.763
This is just too
weird, I'm coming back.

01:05:59.496 --> 01:06:02.234
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

01:06:05.435 --> 01:06:07.371
Hey, where did you come from?

01:06:07.404 --> 01:06:09.975
School trip, the
others have already left.

01:06:10.007 --> 01:06:13.645
(HURRIED DRAMATIC MUSIC)

01:06:27.592 --> 01:06:28.893
And?

01:06:28.926 --> 01:06:31.929
That massive crystal, my
fragment is a part of it.

01:06:31.962 --> 01:06:33.364
Where did you get it from?

01:06:33.397 --> 01:06:35.466
My father says
my mother's family

01:06:35.500 --> 01:06:37.302
has owned it for centuries.

01:06:37.335 --> 01:06:40.304
She was probably
entrusted with a fragment

01:06:40.337 --> 01:06:41.939
so that she could
take care of them.

01:06:43.574 --> 01:06:45.476
Your mother must have
been a powerful sorceress.

01:06:45.509 --> 01:06:46.910
What, why?

01:06:46.944 --> 01:06:49.947
These crystals are only
entrusted to special guardians

01:06:49.980 --> 01:06:52.350
who only exist once
in a generation.

01:06:53.951 --> 01:06:55.753
My father never told me that.

01:06:55.786 --> 01:06:59.690
Your backpack,
changed back in time.

01:07:01.025 --> 01:07:02.027
Maybe also,

01:07:02.060 --> 01:07:02.893
ALL: The book!

01:07:16.507 --> 01:07:20.445
Smells of a child,
no question (GIGGLES).

01:07:21.545 --> 01:07:22.880
It was that vampire brat.

01:07:24.014 --> 01:07:25.850
He was here with
that blood fragment,

01:07:26.984 --> 01:07:29.420
I can still feel his energy.

01:07:29.453 --> 01:07:31.689
The crystal was
almost whole again.

01:07:32.956 --> 01:07:36.328
I have roamed the
world for 1000 years,

01:07:36.360 --> 01:07:37.996
spilled the blood
of the great wizards

01:07:38.029 --> 01:07:42.467
to find and possess every
single fragment of this crystal.

01:07:42.500 --> 01:07:47.339
And now the last
fragment is in the hands

01:07:47.371 --> 01:07:48.906
of this ridiculous child.

01:07:48.940 --> 01:07:49.975
Find this boy!

01:07:52.909 --> 01:07:54.812
Yes, immediately,
there was only

01:07:54.846 --> 01:07:57.949
a teeny weeny display error.

01:08:02.820 --> 01:08:04.056
It's the way it was before.

01:08:08.459 --> 01:08:10.529
Before someone
tore up the pages.

01:08:11.428 --> 01:08:12.963
Even the ink is still damp.

01:08:16.133 --> 01:08:18.535
(SNIFFS) It's
not ink, this is...

01:08:18.569 --> 01:08:20.938
(VLAD RETCHES)

01:08:24.008 --> 01:08:26.578
So notice and tremble.

01:08:26.611 --> 01:08:28.513
NARRATOR: At the 13th hour,

01:08:28.545 --> 01:08:31.982
when Manny's chariot catches
up with his sister's soul

01:08:32.015 --> 01:08:35.652
and overthrows her from
her flaming throne,

01:08:35.685 --> 01:08:38.923
Lucifer will create
his army of darkness

01:08:38.955 --> 01:08:42.060
in the blood red light,
and subdue the world.

01:08:44.562 --> 01:08:46.064
That's really helpful.

01:08:48.566 --> 01:08:51.536
Manny's chariot, who is Manny?

01:08:51.569 --> 01:08:53.871
Guys, it's right here.

01:08:53.904 --> 01:08:55.572
I checked on Magicpedia.

01:08:55.606 --> 01:08:58.042
In Nordic mythology it
was the God who rides

01:08:58.075 --> 01:09:00.746
the moon chariot across
the sky, the sun.

01:09:01.912 --> 01:09:04.915
When Manny topples
his sister's soul

01:09:04.948 --> 01:09:05.984
from the flaming throne.

01:09:06.017 --> 01:09:08.019
It must be the solar eclipse.

01:09:10.854 --> 01:09:11.822
And that's today.

01:09:27.504 --> 01:09:28.139
Take a look.

01:09:32.008 --> 01:09:36.747
It's not possible, Lord
Mayor Ziffer is Lucifer,

01:09:36.779 --> 01:09:39.149
the crystal is in
the Town Hall tower.

01:09:39.182 --> 01:09:41.852
And just below that all
Crailsfelden citizens

01:09:41.886 --> 01:09:43.854
will be gathered for the
solar eclipse festival

01:09:43.886 --> 01:09:45.221
in a few hours.

01:09:45.255 --> 01:09:47.024
And the magical light of
the crystal will hit everyone

01:09:47.057 --> 01:09:48.192
in one fell swoop.

01:09:48.225 --> 01:09:50.962
We can't allow that,
what should we do?

01:09:52.962 --> 01:09:53.997
There's only one way.

01:10:00.637 --> 01:10:02.506
How long will it take?

01:10:02.539 --> 01:10:03.240
Ow!

01:10:03.273 --> 01:10:04.642
What about the boy now?

01:10:16.987 --> 01:10:18.990
They're at the troll bridge!

01:10:19.022 --> 01:10:21.793
(GLASS BREAKS)

01:10:24.995 --> 01:10:29.066
Time is running out, I'll take
care of these kids myself.

01:10:29.100 --> 01:10:31.902
And you can take care of
this bloodsucker's children.

01:10:34.004 --> 01:10:35.005
Yes, boss.

01:10:36.941 --> 01:10:38.043
Okay, off I fly.

01:10:39.075 --> 01:10:41.679
Oops, forgot my broom (GIGGLES).

01:10:49.553 --> 01:10:51.922
Vlad, is there no other way?

01:10:52.990 --> 01:10:53.825
Faye?

01:10:55.058 --> 01:10:56.227
I'm afraid not, Wolf.

01:10:58.161 --> 01:11:01.132
The blood fragment has
to leave Crailsfelden.

01:11:02.299 --> 01:11:04.701
That means I have
to go away forever,

01:11:04.735 --> 01:11:07.672
because otherwise the fragment
will always come back to me.

01:11:09.106 --> 01:11:10.609
We'll come with you.

01:11:14.210 --> 01:11:17.281
And who would take
care of Crailsfelden?

01:11:18.982 --> 01:11:20.118
Elves help and all that.

01:11:21.785 --> 01:11:24.154
(SOMBER MUSIC)

01:12:00.324 --> 01:12:03.128
(WOLF WHINING)

01:12:15.172 --> 01:12:17.642
Young man, are you stupid?

01:12:17.674 --> 01:12:19.177
You are not allowed to leave.

01:12:20.410 --> 01:12:24.782
When time turns backwards
and calamity is high...

01:12:28.185 --> 01:12:33.191
Calamity, okay, well now it
says you can leave Crailsfelden

01:12:34.191 --> 01:12:36.260
and save the town.

01:12:36.293 --> 01:12:38.663
That's all, it
doesn't even rhyme.

01:12:40.297 --> 01:12:41.866
That's good at least.

01:12:43.968 --> 01:12:48.206
But remember, once you
are on the other side,

01:12:48.239 --> 01:12:51.875
you can never come back.

01:12:51.909 --> 01:12:53.277
That's the whole point.

01:12:55.312 --> 01:12:56.147
Right.

01:12:57.947 --> 01:12:59.618
Well then, farewell.

01:13:16.133 --> 01:13:18.269
(WHOOSHING)

01:13:20.236 --> 01:13:21.705
(FAYE SCREAMS)

01:13:21.739 --> 01:13:23.174
Faye!

01:13:23.206 --> 01:13:26.244
(MAGIC CRACKLES)
(FAYE SCREAMS)

01:13:26.276 --> 01:13:28.646
The blood fragment
stays, Tepesh

01:13:29.813 --> 01:13:33.151
You will bring it to the
town hall in one hour,

01:13:33.183 --> 01:13:35.986
or this fairy godmother's
days are over.

01:13:36.020 --> 01:13:36.955
Vlad, no!

01:13:43.093 --> 01:13:45.295
Now there's only
one thing we can do.

01:13:48.732 --> 01:13:51.302
(BELL DINGING)

01:13:59.310 --> 01:14:00.812
Barney.

01:14:09.253 --> 01:14:12.790
Ms. Cercemeyer, how
lovely to see you.

01:14:14.325 --> 01:14:17.462
You know, I'm very worried
about Vlad right now.

01:14:17.495 --> 01:14:19.330
Maybe you could
help me find him?

01:14:19.362 --> 01:14:21.365
Forget your son.

01:14:22.465 --> 01:14:24.134
But you're welcome to adore me

01:14:24.168 --> 01:14:26.871
for the next 100 years, Barney.

01:14:28.371 --> 01:14:32.310
Wonderful, my little batman.

01:14:34.078 --> 01:14:35.245
Just great.

01:14:35.279 --> 01:14:36.114
Oh.

01:15:00.870 --> 01:15:02.806
Are you sure we
shouldn't warn them?

01:15:04.874 --> 01:15:07.044
There's no time
for that, come!

01:15:16.553 --> 01:15:21.057
Has anyone ever told you
what a nice nose you have?

01:15:21.090 --> 01:15:23.427
Oh yes, you noticed?

01:15:23.459 --> 01:15:26.864
And your freckles
sparkle like little bats

01:15:26.896 --> 01:15:27.765
in the full moon.

01:15:31.602 --> 01:15:33.371
What's that at the Town Hall?

01:15:37.106 --> 01:15:37.941
Hmm.

01:15:40.444 --> 01:15:43.214
Looks like black magic, hmm.

01:15:43.246 --> 01:15:46.417
Black magic? (SCOFFS)

01:15:48.017 --> 01:15:51.188
Well, I don't think that,
what are you doing over there?

01:15:53.089 --> 01:15:55.560
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

01:16:00.897 --> 01:16:02.365
What are you doing here?

01:16:02.398 --> 01:16:04.101
Don't give him the fragment!

01:16:04.133 --> 01:16:04.935
Faye!

01:16:04.968 --> 01:16:06.837
And why not?

01:16:06.870 --> 01:16:08.940
You should be grateful to me.

01:16:10.441 --> 01:16:15.446
The crystal will soon
awaken to its full power.

01:16:16.579 --> 01:16:20.250
And then you will be
what you should be again

01:16:20.284 --> 01:16:21.485
under my rule.

01:16:21.517 --> 01:16:24.855
(MAGIC CRACKLING)
(FAYE SCREAMING)

01:16:24.888 --> 01:16:28.293
The blood fragment, Vlad Tepes!

01:16:37.500 --> 01:16:38.335
At last!

01:16:52.650 --> 01:16:55.518
Ah, what are you
looking for there?

01:16:55.552 --> 01:16:58.990
Tohortz telescope, shows
when someone's up to no good.

01:17:06.562 --> 01:17:07.464
Vlad?

01:17:07.498 --> 01:17:10.401
Lord Mayor Ziffer, with horns?

01:17:11.602 --> 01:17:15.340
You and Ziffer are in
cahoots, you bewitched me.

01:17:18.142 --> 01:17:19.377
That's what witches do.

01:17:21.344 --> 01:17:22.946
Toil and trouble.

01:17:24.447 --> 01:17:27.517
You will not stop me
from helping my son.

01:17:31.321 --> 01:17:33.324
(BARNABAS HISSES)

01:17:33.356 --> 01:17:36.026
(HORST HOWLING)

01:17:37.160 --> 01:17:39.630
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

01:18:03.419 --> 01:18:06.156
All the residents
of Crailsfelden

01:18:06.190 --> 01:18:08.426
have gathered under the tower.

01:18:11.527 --> 01:18:12.931
Come on, come on.

01:18:21.070 --> 01:18:26.076
And now I shall create
my army of darkness.

01:18:38.155 --> 01:18:40.657
(CLOCK BONGS)

01:18:44.794 --> 01:18:47.397
Why are you doing all this?

01:18:47.431 --> 01:18:48.331
Three.

01:18:48.365 --> 01:18:50.301
You wouldn't understand.

01:18:50.334 --> 01:18:51.602
Then explain it to me.

